<ext_description linkend="Design_product_data_management_arm.Assembly_alternate_product">

An <b>Assembly_alternate_product</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Product_replacement:arm:Product_replacement_arm.Alternate_product_relationship"/> where the alternate is valid only for a particular design.  The alternate is valid for all instances of the defining_base_product inherited from  <express_ref linkend="Product_replacement:arm:Product_replacement_arm.Alternate_product_relationship"/> within that design.
<note>
In specifying the components to be used in an assembly, it is a
fairly common practice to stipulate that any usage of a given
component (such as referenced by a part number, for example) in that
assembly may be replaced by some other specified 
component.  Each of those other components is then
an <b>Assembly_alternate_product</b> for the specified component
(defining_base_product) for that assembly.  The
<b>Assembly_alternate_product</b> supports only this assembly-level
alternate, that is, it only refers to components that can serve as
alternates for any usage of the specified component (the
<b>basis_context</b>) in that assembly.
</note>
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Design_product_data_management_arm.Assembly_alternate_product.basis_context">
the <b>basis_context</b> specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Unknown:arm:Unknown_arm.Physical_unit_design_view"/> for the <b>Assembly_alternate_product</b>.
</ext_description>
